PRACTICAL APPLICATION

Questions to Ask Yourself

When choosing to use any substance or engage in any behavior:

1. "Am I choosing this from excitement or from anxiety?"

2. "Am I calling this excitement when I'm actually trying to avoid something?"

3. "What am I afraid to investigate in myself?"

4. "Am I trying to fill a hole from the outside?"

5. "Am I dulling my senses to avoid facing something?"

6. "Have I learned the frequency this teacher offers, or am I still dependent on it?"

7. "Can I generate this frequency/state on my own without the substance?"

Investigating Negative Beliefs Without Fear

• Remember: Your existence proves your deservability
• Any belief in unworthiness CANNOT be fundamentally true
• Creation doesn't make mistakes
• If unworthiness were true, you wouldn't exist
• You are necessary for all that is to be all that is
• Knowing this, you can safely investigate any negative belief
• You'll recognize it as just a belief, just a definition
• Not an empirical truth

Using Plant Teachers Correctly

• Use them to learn the frequency they teach
• Understand they're showing you a frequency YOU contain
• Work toward generating that frequency yourself
• This is the higher form of that energy
• The substance is a catalyst, not the goal
• The goal is to embody the frequency without needing the catalyst

Relating to Substances Consciously

• Understand the specific frequency of what you're using
• Form an intentional relationship with it
• Know WHY you're choosing it
• Be honest about whether it's excitement or anxiety
• Recognize societal meanings but form your own relationship
• Use discernment about your true motivations
• Include all parts of yourself holistically rather than creating emptiness

